body:
@axrdb Your issue doesn't sound related to this PR. This fixes an issue with Amazon Redshift timing out. Redshift is a fork of Postgres so shares the hook. 

Re your error, that SQL looks strange, you are using "lists.id" in a join, "lists" looks like a table alias which is not declared. Or is this an array type column? If so I wouldn't recommend joining to it, hard to index those, might explain why it is long running.

If you want to see more in the logging you can start Airflow with DEBUG level logging. I suggest trying a smaller, shorting running version of the query and checking that the connection to gcs is working. You can also check logs on Postgres. I find the pgadmin tool useful.
